## Introduction

This presentation is created to present the final assignment for the Data Sciences Capstone Course, from Coursera course.

The goal of the project is to build a predictive text model. The model will be implemented with a shiny app UI that will predict the next word as the user types a sentence.

It is intended to simulate the functionality of the keyboards of current smartphones, which use the technology of the Swiftkey company.



========================================================

## Application

- The application and the current presentation source codes can be found at https://github.com/hangcyelk/DataScienceCapstoneProject. 5 files are included: ui.R, server.R, bigram.RData, trigram.RData and quadgram.RData
- We need three datasets bigram.RData, trigram.RData and quadgram.RData that can be obtained with the milestone report (https://rpubs.com/byebyedjango/842810). It contains respectively a list of 2 words, 3 words and 4 words.
- The slides presentation is here:https://rpubs.com/byebyedjango/844512


