## Algorithum

### Katz Backoff Model

The Shiny App model was built taking into account the atz Backoff Model.

It is a generative n-gram language model that estimates the conditional probability of a word given its history in the n-gram. It accomplishes this estimation by backing off through progressively shorter history models under certain conditions[1]. By doing so, the model with the most reliable information about a given history is used to provide the better results. 



